scenes.label: *start
texts: ポロン
All right, no one's here yet.
I was at an old-looking apartment building I'd seen through Cross's eyes. There were no hackers or cops here.
モモ
Is this where Flight 302 is being hacked from?
ポロン
That's what we're here to find out.
I got off my graper and headed for the building.
ポロン
Oh yeah! I gotta talk to Oz!
I scrambled to set up a call as I walked.
ポロン
When you make it to the MTIL, ask them for the captain's BMI password.
オズ
...You spyin' on me?
ポロン
No! I'm not even into that... I just need your help to save Flight 302.
ポロン
I'm gonna set up a new channel to the plane, and I need you to get me that password by the time it's ready.
オズ
I'm gonna need you to explain all this.

scenes.label: *bmi
texts: ポロン
There's no time for that! I'm counting on you, bro!
I ended the call before he responded.
We were working towards the same goal, so it'd probably work out.
ポロン
I can worry about that later.
I had to focus on what was in front of me.
I went up the stairs and approached Room 201.
It was an old building, but the security was new—all of the rooms had electronic locks.
I tried the doorknob, but it wouldn't budge. The place was locked.
ポロン
I guess we're the first ones here?

stoptimeline.stoptimeline: 追加_腕c切り替えばたばたループ

texts: It seemed like we were, but I couldn't relax just yet. I had a bad feeling about this, so I went ahead and Saved.
ポロン
...Let's do this.
I used a wire to connect my carrianode to the lock, then hacked into its systems and set it to "open."
ポロン
Too easy.
There was a man through the hallway-kitchen area, but it didn't look like there was anyone else here.
I gave the lock some security software before I took the wire out. It was just a ready-made script, but it'd keep the other hackers busy.
Once Momo and I were in the room, I closed the door behind us.
ポロン
There was an AR image of a plane's cockpit in one corner.
The man in the captain's seat looked serious as he checked the AR meters and adjusted the levers.
It was identical to the Garuda gameplay I'd seen online.
モモ
Pollon, look outside...
Momo pointed outside the AR cockpit.
High-rise buildings towered above the ground. It was clear he was flying over a metropolis.
The AR plane was in the same exact spot as Flight 302, which proved the plane was being hacked from here.
The man's profile matched the customer data too—it was Lime Nukui.
Now we had to figure out if he was taking part in this knowingly...
ライム
ARGHH!
He noticed us and cried out in surprise. The scenery outside the window began to tilt.
ポロン
Straighten it out! You're flying an actual plane here!
ライム
Wh-who are you?! Get out before I call the cops!
モモ
Please, calm down and look at this.
Momo brought up an AR picture of the news. There was an image of 302 banking heavily.
ライム
...No way.
The man nervously corrected the plane in the simulator, straightening out the real 302 in the process.
ライム
You're kidding, right?
モモ
What else do I have to do to make you believe it?
ライム
He was clearly perplexed by all this.
ライム
I-I just ran the game and this stage started up. All I'm doing here is playing it...
モモ
So Kent Korihisa didn't order you to do this?
ライム
Who?
モモ
Cicada 3301. The man behind the quests.
ウインド
Good news! I got some awesome new info!
ウインド
There's actually a flight simulator that—
I couldn't be bothered to explain, so I just shared my vision with him.
ウインド
Huh? What's going on here?
ポロン
I found the Garuda being used for the hack. I'll get 302's flight path from here.
ウインド
You found the source of the hack?! WHOA! FOR REAL?! TAKAOKA, YOU'RE ON FIIIRE!

timelines.label: 追加_腕c切り替えばたばたループ

texts: クロス
So you wanna launch a drone according to the flight path and open an exclusive channel with the plane... No other options?
ポロン
I dunno. I've never been here before.
クロス
All right. I'll help you investigate.
ウインド
Me tooo!
They both got started.
I looked at the Garuda screen again.
ポロン
It's landing in 43 minutes, huh?
That meant that 302 would run out of fuel 12 minutes before the end of the stage.
モモ
What are those rings outside?
Momo pointed at the large, golden rings outside the cockpit.
ライム
They're route rings. I gotta fly through them, and if I go off-course, it's game over.
ポロン
So we can't do an emergency landing from here...
My intuition told me that trying something like that would cut out the plane's guidance data and send it straight down.
クロス
Pollon, I checked the devs' servers but there wasn't any data for this stage.
クロス
Whether to obtain the flight path or to come up with an alternate plan, we'll need to check out the guy's carrianode.
ポロン
All right. I'll set up a backdoor, so you take over.
Cross was better at investigating than I was.
I established a wired connection to Lime's carrianode, then started transferring the app I needed to call Cross over.
